contents2:
A - Superior auricular process

B - Median crest

C - Sacral hiatus

D - Cocyx

E - Posterior sacral foramina

F - Sacral cornu


The sacral hiatus is formed due to the failure of fusion of the 5th and occasionally the 4th sacral lamina resulting in a gap.

The spinal cord ends at the level of L2/3 in children (lower than adult) + The dura ends at the level of S2 in children.

4) According to the regimen of armitage what volume of local anaesthetic is required to achieve the following levels of block?

  • Lumbrosacral 0.5ml/kg
  • Thoracolumbar 1.0ml/kg
  • Mid-thoracic 1.25ml/kg
contents4:
1) Name the labels 1-6 in diagram A : it is a Clarks electrode (as it has a power supply)

  • 1: Anode : Ag/AgCl- (silver/silver chloride)
  • 2: Solution contents: KCL
  • 3: Cathode: platinum
  • 4: battery
  • 5: galvanometer
  • 6: oxygen permeable teflon membrane

2) What is diagram B: Fuel cell

3) Name the labels 1-3 in Diagram B:

  • 1: Cathode: Gold because its in contact with the O2 - and therefore with the e- it can make H20 and OH-
  • 2: Anode : Lead
  • 3: Solution : KCL

4) Why can't a fuel cell be used for breath to breath analysis of O2.

  • slow response time of 20 seconds

5) Name another type of Oxygen analyser?

  • Paramagnetic

(see also Gas and Blood gas monitoring in Physics)
